# Lab One - Minimum Viable Hadoop
The goal is to set up a single node Hadoop cluster on your local machines manually.

## Launch base Docker image
```
# Pull the base image you created in the README and run interactively
$ docker pull 2cdata/minimal_modern_data
$ docker run -i -t 2cdata/minimal_modern_data
```

## Download Hadoop

```
# Create a destination for Hadoop
$ cd /usr

# Download Hadoop
$ wget http://www-us.apache.org/dist/hadoop/common/current2/hadoop-2.9.1.tar.gz
$ wget http://www-us.apache.org/dist/hadoop/common/current2/hadoop-2.9.1.tar.gz.asc
$ wget http://www-us.apache.org/dist/hadoop/common/KEYS

# Verify Hadoop download
$ gpg --import KEYS
$ gpg --verify hadoop-2.9.1.tar.gz.asc hadoop-2.9.1.tar.gz
$ rm KEYS
$ rm hadoop-2.9.1.tar.gz.asc

# Uncompress Hadoop tarball
$ tar zxvf hadoop-2.9.1.tar.gz
$ rm hadoop-2.9.1.tar.gz

# Create a symbolic link to the directory
$ ln -s /usr/hadoop/hadoop-2.9.1 /usr/hadoop 
```
